# Shell scripts and the embedded agent instructions must stay LF: they are
# go:embed-ed and piped to a POSIX shell, so CRLF (from a Windows checkout)
# would break them. Force LF on checkout regardless of core.autocrlf.
*.sh text eol=lf
internal/provision/agent_claude_md.md text eol=lf

# Embedded fonts are binary — never apply line-ending normalization (a CRLF
# munge on a Windows checkout would corrupt the go:embed-ed OTF).
*.otf binary

# Icon assets and the compiled Windows resource object are binary too. A CRLF
# munge on the .syso would corrupt the icon the Go linker embeds into the exe.
*.syso binary
*.png binary
*.ico binary
